    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline>May 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1779</dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>you will be so good as to peruse the inclosed &amp; forward it. I suppose you
                    will be of my mind as to the plan of publication. I hope he has not made his
                    work too large which will hurt the sale. Pray assist him in recommending it to a
                    Bookseller. for I would by all means have him sell it. There may be about 50<hi rend="superscript">L</hi> expence in plates, some of which will be truely
                    curious. I think He may expect 100<hi rend="superscript">L</hi> clear of
                    travelling charges which were 20<hi rend="superscript">L</hi>.<note type="editorial">The above plans relate to <persName ref="pe0156">George
                            Low</persName> and his tours of the Northern Isles.</note></p>
                <p>In a month or two I will send you the specimen of prints for <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0250">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Cordiners
                            Letters</title></bibl>.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>Truely y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline>May 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1779.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
